<p>Created multimodule maven project where folder structure is as below,</p>  <pre><code>|-ProjectA   |-projectB   |-projectC   |-projectD </code></pre>  <p>Created jar of ProjectA using maven shade and AppendingTransformer to include spring handlers,Schema.(Project B uses spring 3.0.7.RELEASE)</p>  <p>Then added this ProjectA jar in eclipse plugin project and build path. One of the eclipse project calls ProjectB.method(); which loads configuration file as,</p>  <pre><code>ClassPathXmlApplicationContext applicationContext = new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("classpath*:META-INF/myfolder/plugin.xml"); </code></pre>  <p>This plugin.xml has</p>  <pre><code> &lt;context:component-scan base-package="mysamplefolderpath" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Problem occurs when it's starts scanning base package in all the jars which are in classpath of eclipse plugin project (eclipse plugin project uses spring 3.0.5.RELEASE).</p>  <p>How can I restrict that base package scan in classpath of ProjectA only?</p>